##Wandering the streets of Wuhan

Wechat, renwumag1980

Feature Introduction, the best Chinese character report

On the morning of February 25, the headquarters for the prevention and control of the new coronavirus pneumonia in Hubei Province issued a notice, "the local government and relevant parties will provide relief services to those who are stranded in Hubei and have difficulties in living due to the control of the li-e channel. ". On the day of the announcement, Xu Xiang (investor) , a native of Yiwu in Zhejiang Province, had been wandering in Wuhan for more than 20 days. He was cowering in an underpass near Wuhan Optics Valley F.C. , along with six other homeless men who had gathered for different reasons. It had just rained heavily in Wuhan and the passageway was slippery, and Xu Xiang (investor) was holding his only two bags as he waited for the sun to come out.

By an eight hour margin, Xu Xiang (investor) was homeless. He had already bought a hard seat ticket back to Yiwu at 6pm on January 23rd and wanted to make a one night stopover in Wuhan. He first learned of the Wuhan outbreak from a street vendor selling face masks.

In Wuhan, the homeless flow in different directions. Some were stationed in hospitals with hot water and leftovers, some in underground parking lots, and the rest, like Xu Xiang (investor) , drifted lonely on benches in different parks. When the city shut down, food, clothing, shelter and transportation became a problem, and they burrowed into every crevice in the city to get what they could.

Cold, hunger, physical pain, overwhelming Xu Xiang (investor) , 48, and the stress of a stagnant life and accumulated debt. For Xu Xiang (investor) , the fall of his life began in 2018. He lost more than 100 square meters of street shops, sometimes he wondered why a lazy do not engage in crooked people, will be so bad?

In the early hours of February 27th, Xu Xiang (investor)'s fall finally took hold. He and three other homeless people were resettled and checked into a hotel. Xu Xiang (investor) told people that for more than 20 days, he finally got a good night's sleep.

Here's Xu Xiang (investor)'s take on the interview, which took place on Feb. 27.

Here's Xu Xiang (investor)'s take on the interview, which took place on Feb. 27.

By Lin Qiuming

Editor | locust tree

1

On the afternoon of January 23, New Year's Day twenty-nine, I arrived at the Wuchang Railway Station. I was surprised when I didn't stop. The station was deserted. There was no one. The entrance is sealed. There's no way in. The staff at the station told me, "the city is closed. "

I'm not from Wuhan, nor am I a migrant worker. I'm just passing through. For the past year, I have been running businesses in both Hangzhou and Yichang. Before the New Year, I ran in Yichang, ready to go home to Yiwu. Yichang has a direct train to Yiwu, but the time is not good, very late. If you transfer from Wuhan to Yiwu, it will be over 6:00 in the morning, and you can have lunch when you get home. So I took a night off in Wuhan and bought a ticket to Yiwu on the twenty-nine pm Chinese calendar. Well, the city's closed. What's a blockade? I thought, probably Wuhan's train or the road section has the question, the repair will be open to traffic.

At this point, someone came up with a bag of masks and said, "do you want a mask? " "why do you need a mask? "I asked. He was like, "you didn't know? Wuhan has an epidemic, to wear a mask. I found out about the pneumonia in Wuhan, so I bought a disposable mask and negotiated a price of 15 yuan.

I thought it wouldn't take long and went back to the hotel. In the next three days, I went to the train station several times, and kept asking the staff on duty outside, when can open? He always said, "until further notice. ". I'm getting flustered, and I'm like, "this is it. This is huge. ".

Every day the hotel raises the price, 130 on the first day, 170 on the second day, and over 200 on the third day. I had to switch hotels, and once the price went over 200, I switched to a cheaper one, back and forth four times. Alcohol was not available, and I cooked the disposable mask repeatedly, boiled it, and dried it with a hair dryer until it had a fur coat on the outside, and then threw it away.

New Year's Eve, I was alone in the hotel, eating a bucket of instant noodles. My wife and kids are back in Zhejiang, and I'm the only one stuck out there. I facetime them, and they look at me, and they don't talk, and they cry.

Before coming to Wuhan, I had less than 2000 yuan on me, and nearly all my money was spent in the hotel. Take-out is one a day. After 11 days at the hotel, there were only 200 more left. By my calculations, we can't live here any longer. We have to eat. Had to check out of the room, carrying a backpack, carrying a bag, out of the hotel, began to stray.

Migrants stranded in Wuhan Sleep in underground garages

2

I didn't know where else to go, and after an hour or two of rambling down the street, I got tired and walked into a park, lay down on a bench, and fell asleep against my backpack. A security guard woke me up and said, "DON'T SLEEP HERE! "where can I sleep? It was only later that I understood what he meant. I could not lie down in a chair, but it was permissible to sit in a chair. I just prop myself up in my backpack and sleep on it.

I can't think of anything to be afraid of. Besides my cell phone and my clothes, what's there to be afraid of? People are afraid of ghosts. How can there be ghosts if no one has seen them? They're bums.

At 4:00 in the morning, I woke up cold. My feet were so cold that I had to get up and walk until seven o'clock in the morning. The Sun came out, and the sun warmed me. Taking advantage of the sunshine, I leaned on a bench by the side of the road and slept for a while, thus passing the first day of vagrancy.

I've slept in so many places in the last 20 days that I'm ashamed to say it. I feel ashamed. I've been to five or six different places, bus stations, parks, movie theaters, basements, places where you can't get out of the rain in the open air, places where you can't get in because you're boarded up, places where it's too cold to sleep at night. The wooden benches in the park are the most comfortable to sleep on. There's a bathroom in the park where you can brush your teeth and wash your face. After the beginning of wandering, I never took a shower to wash his head, there is always a smell.

If I don't sleep, I'm walking. Wuhan Street can not see what people, occasionally encountered a few, staring at me, watching me dragging a backpack, are far away. They know me as a vagabond, and they hate me. But I had to keep moving. It's the only way to get out of the cold. Stop there and boom. Most afraid of rain, no umbrella, can only find shelter under the EAVES, but also can not always stand under the EAVES, must exercise, have to shuttle under different EAVES.

I may not get a meal all day. All the restaurants are closed. There's nothing on the street. I had to order on the take-out platform, swipe it, most of the stores were closed, the rest were expensive, 60,70, where to eat. I only order takeout when I'm too hungry to eat, like today, and the day after that. I've only ordered takeout six times in the last 20-odd days. There is a Chongqing casserole the cheapest take-out, 36 yuan a piece. On One lucky day, I got 26 yuan for the rice, which was the cheapest take-out food. I got a large pool of Chili peppers on the rice, which could only produce two pieces of meat.

A lot of supermarkets are closed. If I could get in, I'd buy a bag of instant noodles. If I couldn't find any water, I'd just chew it. One time I was lucky enough to come across an open supermarket, so I went in and bought some bread. And water. A bottle of mineral water, three dollars, one bottle a day. Sometimes can not buy water, drink tap water in the park bathroom, cold. I can't get any fruit. Without vitamins, I have a sore throat and an ulcer in my mouth.

Wuhan's policy is always changing. The day before yesterday, the supermarket also did not let me in, said only accepts the community group purchase, is collocates the good set meal, the distribution to the resident. I looked everywhere for a place to sell me things. There was a supermarket open in one neighborhood, and I wanted to go in and buy something, but the security guards wouldn't let me in, and they saw me like a plague.

According to the mobile phone map navigation, I marked a route, ready to walk seven days, out of Wuhan. I tried to walk all night. I was cold and hungry, but I couldn't think of anything else. There wasn't enough to eat on the way, and I didn't want to starve to death on the way. Walking in the street, sometimes see the community to the residents to bring food, my heart is so sour. Who knows about US Hobos?

The Park Bench where Xu Xiang (investor) slept

3

I called the shelter a few times, and they said it was out of their hands. I also posted in Wuhan, 58 with the city for help, made 5,6 posts, no response. I know. They think I'm a liar.

When I came to Wuhan, I only had a backpack with three coats in it. These days, I wear all three jackets, two woolens underneath and a leather jacket over them. Yesterday cold, all the pants, three thin pants, also put on. But it's still cold at night. You can fall asleep in the middle of the night, but you always wake up in the middle of the night. When I woke up from the cold, I sat up, holding my feet in my palms for a while. It was so cold that I walked up and down the stairs of the underground passage for half an hour, and some mineral water.

I was homeless for about a week, and on February 12th, I caught a cold. My head was pounding and my throat was killing me, but I didn't have any money, so I called my wife. I told her it was over. She promptly wired me $200. I braced myself and went to the drugstore to buy some cold medicine. There is no boiling water, granules bubble can not open, I pour particles into the mouth, dry swallow, swallow a few mouthfuls of mineral water. At that time, I am not afraid of their new title, the disease is better, at least some people to care about me. I bought a second mask, 29.8, either an N95 or a plain cotton mask. My heart is killing me. 30 Bucks, a meal, a few days of my life.

No matter how tired, I have to find a place to charge my cell phone, most afraid of the cell phone battery, the family can not find me. Yesterday I ran for half an hour before I saw a bank at the Fujiapo long-distance bus station. These days I notice a pattern: The bank's ATM machine has an unassuming socket under it that can be recharged. The charge is slow, it starts at noon and is not charged until 6 pm. In order to charge faster, I do not dare to use the phone, just sitting on the edge of the afternoon. I got sleepy sitting down, fell asleep on the tile floor.

Lost in confusion, I saw some people from my front walk, Chengguan, food delivery, disinfection, and a broom, from me less than 5 meters. They didn't even ask me why I slept here. It's like they didn't even see me.

The tunnel where Xu Xiang (investor) slept

4

After graduating from junior high school, I worked as an assembly line worker in a garment factory for more than ten years. In 2016, I finally saved up enough money and borrowed some from others. I opened a mobile phone store outside a shopping mall in Yiwu. The store is quite large, with more than 100 square meters. In those years, the phone business was booming, making two hundred thousand a year. I thought everything was on track. I took out a loan to buy a house for my son. Unexpectedly, after 2018, the industry began to decline, people are more willing to buy mobile phones online, more and more difficult to operate physical stores, can only barely break even, not to make any money. Buy Today, ship tomorrow, a machine may drop 100 or 200. The losses snowballed as they accumulated.

Last March, I was defrauded of a payment. When the purchase, the other side let me send the goods to him, have not given me money on no longer contact. I called the police, but it didn't help. There's an indictment fee, and we won't get it back in two or three years. In May, Yiwu under a particularly heavy rain, the store was flooded in the middle of the night, the mobile phone in the cabinet was flooded, the loss of more than 100,000. I looked at a cell phone, tears desperately fall, hard to run two or three years of the store so collapsed.

The shop closed down, lost more than a million, owed friends more than 200,000, but also with 300,000 mortgage, I had to start working again. This year, the New Year, the wife said, do not mind the burden is too heavy, years or to pass. I think, the wife is right, then happy to go back to the new year, but did not expect to happen this matter. It was in the water, and now it's on ice.

I don't understand. We're not lazy, we don't like to gamble, and we're not crooked. I work diligently, save money, how come these natural and man-made disasters, so not smooth?

My wife called me, crying on the other end, and I knew there was nothing she could do. My son is in his early 20s. He just went to work this year. He is still an apprentice. He didn't get paid. Now the factory is closed again. I don't know when he will be able to go back to work. They asked me where I slept at night, and I was afraid to say. My wife tried to get some money to call me, but she ran out. Yesterday, a volunteer gave me $100. That's all I had.

The day before yesterday, I was sitting in the park, and I got a call from a friend. I owe him $50,000. His mother has cancer and needs money. I had to borrow $6,000 from another friend to pay him back some of it.

Wuhan Snow Day (February 15) , is my most painful time. It's getting cold. It's cold. At 5 am, I was sitting in a chair outside a movie theater, leaning against my bag, looking up at the sky, hoping for an early morning. I watched the moon come out and go in, but I didn't wait for the sun. It was about noon, and there was snow in the sky. The snow was falling all over my face. My feet were so cold that I had to get up and walk around. Luckily, there was a leather coat and a sun hat to keep out the snow and rain. Dripping everywhere, no place to lie down, I walked on an overpass. Looking at his own shadow, tears flow down. I am a big man, rarely cry, this time really shed tears. I was looking at the bridge and I wanted to kill myself.

But I didn't jump. I can't let it go and leave the burden on my wife and kids.

Wuhan Street View Yin Xi far shot

5

In Wuhan, and I like a lot of people, but will not gather together, are hiding. Some are like me, just passing through Wuhan, some are working in Wuhan. People don't talk much when they see each other.

I've been alone for 20 days, since I was a vagabond. The other day, I met a couple of other homeless people at the Yellow Crane Tower, so to speak. After that, I slept with them in the underpass by the park. Seven of them.

The day before yesterday, I picked up two foam board Mat in the roadside, pad under the body, sleep to feel better. It was the first time I ever picked up anything on the side of the road. I do not want to pick up garbage, dumpster, feel unsanitary, not decent. That night, it began to rain heavily in Wuhan, I put clothes on the body, repeatedly unable to sleep, cold. The rain ran down the stairs and the wind blew in through the exits on both sides of the walkway.

Last night, a volunteer gave us a quilt and a tent. Thank you very much. A few of US put the tent cloth on the bottom, and the two beds were covered separately. We were very happy. Finally, a quilt. Someone asked me if I could borrow his quilt to put under it? I didn't ask for it. He has only one quilt of his own. Wouldn't it be colder if he lent me one?

A few volunteers brought us food, a bag of peanut butter cookies, a bottle of water, chicken in the lunch box, and dumplings. The food was so hot, I ate it in five minutes. And 10 disposable masks. I count two days with a mask, can hold for a period of time, but also afraid of the city too long, in the future if there is no mask, the supermarket won't let, even can not buy food.

I've been on the road so long, I don't know what time it is. Yesterday I was asked my age, I just remembered, today is February fifth, my birthday, I am 48 years old. What do you wish for? If there is a cup of hot water in front of me to drink, I will be satisfied, the heart of a warm. I don't want anything else. It's too remote.

Perhaps the volunteers reflected this problem, at 1:00 this morning, several men in uniform went to the underground passage, registered our information, took our temperature, took four people including me, the other three were still there, i don't know why they didn't leave together.

The uniformed men took us to a nearby hotel and put us up. There was hot water in the hotel. I took a hot bath and felt much more relaxed. I got a good night's sleep and didn't wake up until 11 am. It was so comfortable that I didn't turn over. Today, I woke up and looked in the mirror. I found that my hair was half white during the time I was in Wuhan.

The innkeeper cooked dinner and asked us to join him. It is not clear who will pay for the hotel or how long it will last. No one told us that. The volunteers contacted me and asked me how my stay was, to put my mind at ease. If it wasn't for them, I don't know what would have happened.

As soon as this is over, I'll start over. I think, to help themselves up, slowly pick up the business, worthy of family, worthy of friends. Go back again difficult, also want to face others, the money that should return should return, want to think of a way, I can not cold other people's heart.

Xu Xiang (investor) was given an alias at the request of the interviewee
